DISTRIBUTION, HABITAT AND PHENOLOGY. — Eastern coast of Grande Terre and locally common around Baie de Tina (
Fig. 6
); in sclerophyllous forests among hills, sometimes behind mangroves, on black clays or soils derived from schists or calcareous schists; 

5- 
100 m

. Flowering December through May; fruiting December through October.
